The paper deals with computer vision tasks such as optical flow estimation and patch matching, which are typically covered under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also extensively uses deep learning techniques, specifically convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which are covered under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the evaluation of the robustness of trained features, which is related to robotics (cs.RO) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
